“Quumble” doesn’t appear to be a standard English word. It may be:

- a typo or mishearing of **grumble**, **quibble**, or **quabble**;
- a rare slang term or a made-up word;
- a name/brand in a specific community.

If you meant **quibble**, that means a minor objection or to argue about small details. If you meant **grumble**, that means to complain quietly or mutter in annoyance. ([merriam-webster.com](https://www.merriam-webster.com/dictionary/quibble?utm_source=openai))

